NAME
	capitalize - capitalize the first word of a string
	
SYNOPSIS
	string capitalize(string str|int foobar, void|int)

DESCRIPTION
	With this command the first letter of a string is made
	upper-case. If the argument given is an integer, a 0 is
	returned.

	If a second argument not 0 is provided, the entire string
	is capitalized and returned.

SEE ALSO
	lower_case


